						               													<description>Ardennes Plus is a grand strategic level simulation of 20th century conflicts in the densely forested and rough terrain of the Ardennes region of France, Luxembourg and Belgium.  This game features scenarios have been created for the Battle of the Bulge WWII December 1944.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game uses Army level command structures to simulate supply and command in divisional and corps level units.  The game optionally represents the fog of war that was very common in the rough country of the Ardennes, by offering 2 hidden movement systems.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The low counter density, and high map scale is used to create conditions for fast play and resolution is possible in less than 2 hours. Event card options are also incldued to add historical flavour to this classic battle, based on the geopolitic and technical events that occured at the time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game can be played solo, as a two player game, with one player commanding the Allied forces, and one the German forces, or as a three player game, with two players playing the Allied forces (one playing Commonwealth forces and one playing USA forces), and the third player commanding the German forces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
